    <title>Subdivision and spline spaces</title>
    <summary>  A standard construction in approximation theory is mesh refinement. For a
simplicial or polyhedral mesh D in R^k, we study the subdivision D' obtained by
subdividing a maximal cell of D. We give sufficient conditions for the module
of splines on D' to split as the direct sum of splines on D and splines on the
subdivided cell. As a consequence, we obtain dimension formulas and explicit
bases for several commonly used subdivisions and their multivariate
generalizations.
</summary>
